<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=faryn98&buddyTimeStamp=20070315&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.millsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1174162270&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>May</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>May's home at <a href='/home/?user=faryn98'>71185 Broadway Boulevard</a> has become a prime hanging-out spot for all of Millsberry's fashion lovers. Since May moved in on August 2, 2005, she has made many friends who routinely stop by her Metro Park pad for style advice.<br><br>Why all the attention? May has a sense of style that everyone wants! There's something about the colors and patterns she puts together, along with her confidence in her fashion choices, that makes her a total trendsetter. When she has guests over, she lets them try on her funky clothes, serves food, and trades the latest gossip (there's always something juicy to talk about!).<br><br>Another thing that makes May stand out is her passion for the cosmos. She's a budding astronomer who was floored when Jenneira made her appearance in Millsberry. May had always suspected there was other life in the universe, and she was so happy to encounter such a sweet and interesting (and stylish) extra-terrestrial.<br><br>May has always stood out and attracted attention, but remains a totally sweet, down-to-earth girl anyone can talk to. Be sure to say hi if you see her at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Clothing Store</a>! <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, May, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
